task.summary: Added MQTT connection, Module Support, Menu Screen, loading screen and a basic lights module. Working on actual lights connection through the broker.
MQTT PROTOCOL IS WORKING IN HERE TOO! Communication has been setup, time to do the actual magic.
So... creating light sections now works and the server also knows you are doing it
Creating light sections and turning them on works. There's a couple bugs here and there that I need to fix though.
Updated command parsing a bit, still needs a lot of reworking.
Loads a bit of data from the server, doesn't need lights creation every single time
Working on LightSection arguments, to have multiple LightSections in a single bluetooth peripheral.
Started working on a custom voice assistant using snowboy and Google Speech Recognition.
